  <body style="              width: 1455px;"> <title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""
      id="Font"> </title:>
    <div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><title:
          blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
          <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Blood: Fresh Supply</strong></p>
          <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Monolith Productions - 1997 -
              PC</strong></p>
          <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nightdive Studios - 2019 - PC</strong></p>
        </title:></span></div>
    <title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
          style="color: #000099;"> </span></span>
      <p style="text-align: center;"> </p>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> </span></span>
      <p style="text-align: left;"> <span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><i>I
            live, again...</i> How fitting for this re-release of one of the
          "holy trinity" of games made with Build Engine: Duke Nukem 3D, Shadow
          Warrior and Blood.</span></p>
      <span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"> </span>
      <p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">Running
          on the KEX Engine by the talented developer Samuel Villarreal the game
          shines with a 60fps constant framerate and DX11 / OpenGL and even a
          Vulkan renderer. The only downside about the DX render is that you
          cannot use the overlay or take screenshots unless you run the game in
          windowed or borderless mode. Not a huge deal but still annoying.</span></p>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"><span style="color: #66ff99;">
          </span><br>
        </span></span>
      <p> </p>
      <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
              src="images/Blood/Blood4.jpg" "="" id="border"><br>
          </span></span> </div>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> <br>
        </span></span>
      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">I
                admit I spent quite some times looking at all those amazing
                rooms rendered in DX11.</span><br>
            </span></span></span></div>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> <br>
          <br>
        </span></span>
      <p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;">
            <span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span style="color: black;">The
                plot is barebone like every other fps before the arrival of the
                two colossus that began the narrative shooter genre: Half-Life
                &amp; Unreal. <br>
                The story begins with the protagonist and cultist Caleb getting
                killed with his friends by the dark god T'chernobog. After he
                discovers to be still alive, Caleb decides to get revenge by
                mass murdering <i> everything he sees </i>. Talk about having
                a wicked sense of justice. </span></span></span></span></p>
      <span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"> <br>
      </span>
      <p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">
          The game is divided into 4 chapters plus two expansions called <i>
            Plasma Pak </i> and <i> Cryptic Passage </i> which are both
          selectable from the main menu. <br>
          The first chapter is arguably the most difficult one: you will learn
          how to chuck barrels of dynamite (which takes a bit of time), to use
          ammo properly, since you will experience shortages in the first
          levels.&nbsp;</span></p>
      <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
              src="images/Blood/Blood7.jpg" "="" id="border"><br>
          </span></span> </div>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> </span></span>
      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Meet
                your new friend,the dynamite bundle</span><br>
            </span></span></span></div>
      <p></p>
      <p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">
        </span><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"><span
              style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span style="color: black;"><br>
                Every fight feels like a little puzzle with multiple ways to
                solve it, from going guns blazing to abuse the unique weakness
                of every enemy. </span></span><br>
          </span></span> </p>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> </span></span>
      <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border:7px white; "
              src="images/Blood/Blood1.jpg" alt=""><br>
          </span></span> </div>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> <br>
        </span></span>
      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
            style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">One
                of the best feeling you can get: a room full of cultist and a
                loaded shotgun ready to blast some holes.</span><br>
            </span></span></span></div>
      <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;"> <span
            style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><br>
          </span></span></span>
      <div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #336666;"><span
              style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">
                <span style="color: black;">The main chapters feels very diverse
                  one to the another in both terms of enemy variety, ammo count
                  and backgrounds. <br>
                  Caleb goes in the first chapter from his grave to a chapel
                  then he finds himself in a train station fighting his way to
                  the last train. After delibertly derailing it he visits a Luna
                  Park and in the end he reaches the boss: a giant Stone
                  Gargoyle related to her lover Ophelia.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></div>
      <div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #336666;"><span
              style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span
                  style="color: black;"><br>
                </span></span></span></span></span></div>
      <div style="text-align: center;"><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""></title:>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
          <div style="text-align: center;"><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
              <div style="text-align: left;">
                <div style="text-align: center;">
                  <div style="text-align: center;"><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""></title:><title:
                      blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                            style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
                              src="images/Blood/Blood2.jpg" "="" id="border"></span></span></div>
                    </title:><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                            style="color: #000099;"></span></span></div>
                    </title:><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                          style="color: #000099;"><br>
                        </span></span></title:><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                            style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span
                                style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">This
                                is the best time to introduce him to your new
                                toy: the Napalm Launcher!</span></span></span></span></div>
                    </title:><br>
                    <title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                      <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                            style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;">
                            </span></span></span></div>
                    </title:><title: blood:="" fresh="" supply=""> <br>
                      <title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                        <div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                              style="color: #336666;"><span style="color: #000099;"><span
                                  style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span
                                    style="color: black;"></span></span></span></span></span></div>
                      </title:></title:></div>
                  <title: blood:="" fresh="" supply="">
                    <div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                          style="color: #336666;"><span style="color: #000099;"><span
                              style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span style="color: black;"></span></span></span></span></span><title:
                        blood:="" fresh="" supply=""></title:><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                          style="color: #336666;"><span style="color: #000099;"><span
                              style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span style="color: black;">The
                                two expansions feel very different from the main
                                game: while Plasma Pak was built <i> in house </i>
                                by Monolith, <i> Cryptic Passage </i> was not.
                              </span></span></span></span></span></div>
                  </title:><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #336666;"><span
                        style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span
                            style="color: black;"></span></span></span></span></span></div>
                <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #336666;"><span
                      style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;"><span
                          style="color: black;"> I really didn't like Cryptic
                          Passage: while it had huge environments to explore, it
                          felt really empty and boring, without that distinct
                          feel of actually doing something than just finding
                          keys and blowing up cultists. <br>
                          The final boss was just terrible, a quick rip off by
                          picking the Cerberus boss in chapter 3 and doubling it
                          in a very small area. Just a bad design overall. <br>
                          <br>
                          <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                                style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
                                  src="images/Blood/Blood5.jpg" "="" id="border"><br>
                              </span></span> </div>
                          <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;">
                            </span></span>
                          <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                                style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span
                                    style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">I
                                    just fought a couple of zombies here. So
                                    much free space wasted...</span><br>
                                </span></span></span></div>
                          <br>
                          <br>
                          Plasma Pak felt like a palette cleanser after Cryptic
                          Passage: it picks up after the end of the main game
                          and introduces new alt-fires for some weapons such as
                          the Napalm Launcher and new type of enemies like the <i>
                            Mini Calebs </i>. <br>
                          <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                                style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
                                  src="images/Blood/Blood6.jpg" "="" id="border"><br>
                              </span></span> </div>
                          <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;">
                            </span></span>
                          <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                                style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span
                                    style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Those
                                    small clones are perky bastards, if you've
                                    got a spare dynamite blow 'em up for good.</span><br>
                                </span></span></span></div>
                          <br>
                          <br>
                          The boss fight was just amazing! Three cultist that
                          once received enough damage they trasform into the
                          real boss called <i>The Beauty and the Beasts.</i> <br>
                          <br>
                          It was really fun to do all the achievements, in the
                          end I took a total of 30hrs to finish it 100% on the
                          Well Done difficulty, which is hard as nails. <br>
                        </span><br>
                        <div style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                              style="color: #000099;"><img style="width: 842px; height: 501px; border-bottom-style: none;"
                                src="images/Blood/Blood3.jpg" "="" id="border"><br>
                            </span></span> </div>
                        <span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span style="color: #000099;">
                          </span></span>
                        <div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Cambria;"><span
                              style="color: #000099;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><span
                                  style="color: black; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
                                  Heeeeeeere's Johnny!</span><br>
                                <br>
                              </span></span></span></div>
                        <i> <span style="color: black;">Really, really
                            recommended to pick up for dirt cheap on a Steam
                            discount, definitely worth the price. </span></i></span><span
                        style="color: black;"><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">
                        </span><b><span style="font-family: Lucida Sans Unicode;">
                            9/10 </span><br>
                        </b></span></span></span></span></div>
            </title:></div>
